                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d806">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11 Am 8/16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-13T16:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 13, 1921—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 14—10:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>37. Department’s 22, November 30, 6 p.m. President’s answer received today states
                    that by reason of autonomy of municipality he will not be able to intervene but
                    that he has written the municipality <pb facs="1001" n="877" xml:id="pg_877"/>
                    transcribing at the same time the desires of Amsinck and Company and suggesting
                    to the president of the municipality the necessity that the municipality comply
                    with the arrangement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
